summary: ENB settings for Skyrim that will make everyone who doesn\'t own the game cry. Variable performance options, only a 4 FPS hit with the high-performance settings.
descriptionHtml:
[SIZE=6][center][I][URL=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/9930]Revamped Exterior Fog[/URL] is an pre-requisite for this ENB!![/I][/center][/SIZE]

[center][IMG]http://img853.imageshack.us/img853/2320/ssedit1.jpg[/IMG][/center]

[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Introduction:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
This is an artistic realistic ENB suite based on ENB 0.119, the screenshots speak for themselves. These settings are designed for Vanilla Skyrim, although I am open to tweaking them for CoT/UWRL/RL if desired.

[center][B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Videos[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B][/center]
[center]Hodilton recordred a great video, as always, do check it out![/center]

[center][youtube]RsluzuaDVks[/youtube][youtube]22ao2pICeJ8[/youtube][/center]

[center][IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img708/2746/screenshot138nu.jpg[/IMG]
[/center]


[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Credits First![/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
[LIST][*]Many great ENB suites need to be credited for this one as these settings are designed with guidance from them. 
[*][URL=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=4142]CLENB[/URL] by HD6
[*][URL=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/25578]Jasmin ENB v5_2 Real[/URL] by r6angel. 
[*]The DoF settings used here are tweaked versions of the one designed by Matso for [URL=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/5587]Skyrim Visual Immersion[/URL].
[*][URL=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/20781]Project ENB[/URL] by bronze316.
[*]And of course Boris for ENB, we are after all, just tweakers.
[/LIST]


[center][IMG]http://img832.imageshack.us/img832/9113/screenshot196s.jpg[/IMG][/center]
[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Description:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
Sky-Real ENB is an attempt by me to design a realistic-saturated ENB suite based on clear summer days. Unfortunately no ENB can be designed keeping each and every weather template and every diffirent area in Skyrim in mind, hence oversaturation/overcontrast may occur occassionally in certain weather types/ certain times of the day, though I have tried to avoid both as far as possible.

I hope you enjoy using this ENB as much as I did tweaking it! 


[center][IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img163/8335/screenshot227p.jpg[/IMG][/center]

[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Installation:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
[LIST][*]Download ENB 0.119 from [url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0119.htm]here[/url].
[*]Extract the 0.119 file, and copy all contents inside the \'Wrapper\' folder to your skyrim root directory. (Where tesV.exe is)
[*]Download and extract this ENB\'s files in any location. (Not skyrim root!)
[*]Copy all files inside the \'Core Files\' folder to your skyrim root directory. Overwrite if prompted.
[*]Open the \'Optional Performance Settings\' folder and select your performance option, copy it to your skyrim root directory. (Check \'FPS Notes\' for the performance impact of each setting)
[*]Run Skyrim!
[*]OPTIONAL: If required select files from the \'Optional Effects\' folder, and replace the default ones in your skyrim root directory.
[/LIST]

[center][IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img856/3692/screenshot92y.jpg[/IMG][/center] 

[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Known Issues:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
[LIST][*]If you cant see anything underwater use [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=14007]Green Water Fix[/url]
[*]Patch 1.5 causes ENB SSAO to make water in Skyrim transparent, if this is a problem for you, use one of the performance options which has SSAO disabled.
[*]Mobile GPU users (Mostly Nvidia Optimus), or any one else who faces absurdly low FPS as soon as you install an ENB, use the \'Injector\' version of ENB.
[*]Always always while using ENB, make sure that bfloatpointrendertarget=1 in skyrimperfs.ini!
[/LIST]

[center][IMG]http://img833.imageshack.us/img833/7959/screenshot315z.jpg[/IMG][/center]

[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Mods that I use and Highly Recommend:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
[LIST]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/4805]AOF Detailed Mountains[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/3385]Lush Trees[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/3288]Lush Grass[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/24364]AOF HD Tree LODs[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/1598]Enhanced Distant Terrain[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/85]Enhanced Night Skyrim[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/9930]Revamped Exterior Fog[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/4834]High Quality LODs[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/12866]Skyrim Distant Detail[/url]
[*][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/607]Skyrim HD - 2K Textures[/url]
[/LIST]
Install the mods only if you have performance to spare! Most of them are basically making your system render more polygons and process more textures, but they make a huge difference in making the distant terrain in Skyrim acceptable to look at.  

[center][IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img856/6257/screenshot266v.jpg[/IMG][/center]

[B][COLOR=#7f7f7f][SIZE=6][FONT=Garamond]Tweaking:[/FONT][/SIZE][/COLOR][/B]
[LIST][*]First of all check if what you need is included in the Optional files!!
[*]Please refer to my older [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/15551]ENB\'s page[/url] for a basic ENB tweaking guide.
[/LIST]

[center][IMG]http://imageshack.us/a/img705/8748/screenshot55gw.jpg[/IMG][/center]
